    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset combines geospatial coordinates (latitude/longitude pairs) with categorical flight frequency data across three dimensions: location (2D geospatial), airport size (ordinal via marker radius), and route density (quantitative via line thickness). Synthetic data maintains realistic airport positions (\u03bc accuracy \u00b10.05\u00b0) and flight frequencies following a Pareto distribution where 20% of airports handle 80% of traffic. The basemap provides spatial context while bubble encoding follows Stevens' power law for accurate magnitude perception. Curved flight paths leverage B\u00e9zier curves to maintain geographic relationships while avoiding overlap. Color choices (red-yellow-green diverging scheme) comply with CVD-safe palettes while maintaining pre-attentive pop-out effects for hub identification. Statistical coherence is maintained through marker radii scaled to \u221a(flight count) for accurate area perception."
